Halilhodzic impressed at last year's World Cup in Brazil when he guided African nation Algeria into the knockout stages  for the first time, only to lose 2-1 in extra time to eventual winners Germany. 

The one-time Ivory Coast coach is expected to arrive in Japan on Friday to complete the deal.

